              "datalab-41aef1f5efab13d4f38f69e86c726062_img.jpg": {
                "description": "Diagram of an artificial neuron j. Inputs x0=1 (bias), x1, x2, x3, ..., xn are connected to weights w0j, w1j, w2j, w3j, ..., wnj. The weighted inputs are summed (Σ) to produce vj, which is then passed through an activation function f to produce the output yj.",
                "source": "datalab",
                "described_at": "2026-05-13T16:14:00",
                "type": "generico",
                "include": true
