                "description": "Diagram of an artificial neuron j. Inputs x0, x1, x2, x3, ..., xn are shown on the left. x0 is a bias term with x0 = 1. Each input is connected to a weight node (w0j, w1j, w2j, w3j, ..., wnj). The weights are then summed in a summation node (Σ). The result is passed to an activation function node (f). The output is labeled 'Saida' and yj. A label 'Pesos' is placed near the summation node. A label 'Peso extra conhecido como bias' is placed near the bias weight w0j.",
                "source": "datalab",
