              "datalab-284768c5ee1a05aa1b9ce396f606a040_img.jpg": {
                "description": "A flowchart illustrating the architecture of a conversational agent. The process starts with 'Input from User' leading to 'Speech Recognition', which outputs a 'Word Sequence' to 'NL Understanding'. 'NL Understanding' uses 'World Knowledge' and produces a 'Semantic Interpretation'. A decision diamond '?' evaluates if the interpretation is 'incomplete' or 'complete'. If 'incomplete', it goes to 'Dialog Management', which uses 'Interaction Context' and sends a 'Clarifying Question' via 'Speech Synthesis' back to the user. 'Dialog Management' also identifies 'Missing Elements'. If 'complete', it goes to 'Action Selection', which uses 'World Knowledge' and produces an 'Inferred User Intent' and 'Best Outcome'. 'Action Selection' then uses 'Speech Synthesis' to produce an 'Output to User'. A feedback loop labeled 'Elicitation' connects the output back to the initial input.",
                "source": "datalab",
                "described_at": "2026-05-13T16:25:01",
                "type": "generico",
                "include": true
              },
              "datalab-6217eb6fdcc300d854c2ba3651151539_img.jpg": {
