              "datalab-20727e57890be6da5692a02d13c0a8ec_img.jpg": {
                "description": "Underfitting in regression: A straight line is drawn through a set of blue data points that form a clear upward curve, failing to capture the underlying trend. Optimal fitting in regression: A smooth, parabolic curve is drawn through the blue data points, capturing the underlying trend. Overfitting in regression: A highly complex, jagged line is drawn through the blue data points, capturing every individual point but failing to capture the overall trend. Underfitting in classification: A single straight line is drawn through a set of blue and red data points, failing to separate the two classes effectively. Optimal fitting in classification: A smooth, curved boundary is drawn between the blue and red data points, separating the two classes. Overfitting in classification: A highly complex, jagged boundary is drawn between the blue and red data points, separating every individual point but failing to capture the overall pattern.",
                "source": "datalab",
                "described_at": "2026-06-19T05:56:41+00:00",
                "type": "generico",
                "include": true
              },
