                "description": "A 2D plot showing the OR function's decision boundary. The horizontal axis is labeled x1 and the vertical axis is labeled x2. Both axes have tick marks at 0 and 1. Four blue circular data points are plotted at coordinates (0,0), (0,1), (1,0), and (1,1). A solid black line, representing the decision boundary, passes through the points (0,1) and (1,0). The region below and to the left of this line (where x1 + x2 < 1) is the region where the output is 0. The region above and to the right of the line (where x1 + x2 > 1) is the region where the output is 1.",
                "source": "datalab",
