                "description": "Diagram illustrating the Minimax algorithm for a 3x3 tic-tac-toe game. The tree starts with an initial state (empty 3x3 grid). A MAX node (X's turn) branches into three possible moves. Each move leads to a MIN node (O's turn), which branches into all possible responses. The tree continues to terminal states (win, loss, or draw) where the objective function is evaluated as -1, 0, or +1.",
